Use an Append node in a Data Prep recipe in CRM Analytics to stack rows from multiple sets of input data into one dataset. For example, use this node to combine sales records from two different Salesforce orgs, each containing sales transactions from a specific region.

In a Data Prep recipe that already has at least one Input node, select the Add Node button between two nodes or at the end of the recipe. To show the Add Node button between two nodes, hover the cursor on the connecting line.
Select Append in the Add Node box.
Select the data to append and choose which columns to include.
Data Prep automatically maps columns from both sets of input data based on matching column names.

If a column is mapped for one source and not the other, the Append node inserts null values for all source rows to which the column doesnâ€™t apply. To map two columns, enter the column name from the appended rows next to its corresponding recipe column.
Click Apply to add the node to the recipe.
Save the recipe.

When you run the recipe, the Append node combines rows from both sets of input data into the same dataset.
title: Using Append Node in Data Prep
